                        <h2>
                            Mindfulness Of The Breath and The Body In Movement
                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            ‘Use the breath as an anchor to tether your attention to the present moment.  Your thinking mind will drift here and there, depending  on the currents and winds moving in the mind, at some point, the anchor line grows taut and brings you back.’  John Kabat – Zinn (1994).
                            <br />
                            There is pleasure and power in being present.  Attending to and investigating the ways things are in the body and mind in the present moment through the practice of attention on the breath and mindful movement. In this session we will be exploring several distinct yet interrelated formal meditation practices.

                        </p>

