                        <h2>
                            Focusing on the breath

                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            Focusing on the breath brings you back to this very moment, the here and now.  The breath is always available as an anchor and a haven to come back to no matter where you are or what is happening.
                            Focusing on the breath can change your experience by connecting you with a space and potentially broader perspective from which to view things.

                        </p>
                        <h2>
                            Basics of sitting

                        </h2>
                        <p>
                            It helps to adopt an erect and dignified posture, with your head, neck, and back aligned vertically.  The aim is to adopt the physical counterpart of the inner attitudes of self-reliance, self-acceptance, patience, and alert attention that we are cultivating during the practice of meditation.
